# Screen Interaction Design

When the user asks for screen specifications, UI prototypes, interaction flows, or screen-story traceability, follow the workflow defined in this project's `.agents/skills/screen-interaction-design/core/workflow.md`.

## Quick Reference

1. **Phase 1 — Screen Inventory**: Read input artifacts (user stories, functional design), list all screens with states. Use `.agents/skills/screen-interaction-design/core/screen-states-checklist.md` for state identification.
2. **Phase 2 — Screen Design**: Generate self-contained HTML prototypes per screen with state switchers. Use `.agents/skills/screen-interaction-design/assets/prototype-boilerplate.html` as starting point.
3. **Phase 3 — Interaction Flow**: Document step-by-step user journeys. Use `.agents/skills/screen-interaction-design/core/interaction-flow-template.md`.
4. **Phase 4 — Validation**: Verify prototypes with browser testing and capture screenshots.
5. **Phase 5 — Traceability**: Map screens to user stories, produce gap report.

## Output Location

All outputs go to `aidlc-docs/discovery/screen-design/`.

## Templates

- Screen spec: `.agents/skills/screen-interaction-design/core/screen-spec-template.md`
- Interaction flow: `.agents/skills/screen-interaction-design/core/interaction-flow-template.md`
- Artifact schemas: `.agents/skills/screen-interaction-design/core/artifact-contract.md`

## Key Rule

Always get user approval on the screen inventory (Phase 1) before generating prototypes (Phase 2).
